hetik zwischen Drama und Performance, zwischen Konflikt- und Überschreitungsdramaturgie.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aExistentialism in literature. 0aGerman dramaxHistory and criticism. 0aOther (Philosophy) in literature. 0aTheaterzGermanyxHistory. 4aDer Andere. 4aDramaturgie. 4aIdentität. 4aKulturtheorie. 4aLiteraturwissenschaft. 4aMedien. 4aMediengeschichte. 4aSelektion. 4aTheaterwissenschaft. 4aÄsthetik. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Theater / History & Criticism.2bisacsh  aAesthetics.  aCultural Theory.  aLiterary Studies.  aMedia History.  aMedia.  aTheatre Studies.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2017z978311071954308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Arts 2018z9783110603088oZDB-23-DPK08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2018z9783110603255oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyterttranscript: Complete eBook-Package 2014z9783110401226oZDB-23-TGP40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783839424001zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783839424001423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783839424001/original  a978-3-11-071954-3  DG Plus eBook-Package 2017b2017  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_MUAR  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGGb2017  aZDB-23-DPKb2018  aZDB-23-TGPb2014